## Notes

Every processing stage should satisfy the following principles:

- Single Responsibility
- Explainability
- Traceability
- Deterministic Behavior
- Explicit Inputs
- Explicit Outputs

A processing stage must never assume the responsibility of another theoretical layer.

No pipeline may bypass the Educational Knowledge Model.

Educational knowledge must always evolve progressively through the architecture.